HEADWORD: Lexiphanic
<hw>Lex`i*phan"ic</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧ks`⟦icr⟧*f⟦acr⟧n"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>lexifa`nis</grk> a phrase monger;
<grk>le`xis</grk> speech + <grk>fai`nein</grk> to show.]</ety>
<def>Using, or interlarded with, pretentious words; bombastic; <as>as, a
<ex>lexiphanic</ex> writer or speaker; <ex>lexiphanic</ex>
writing.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lexiphanicism</ent>⟦br⟧
